{
  "stem": "1033.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I used to lose myself with other kids, and that was-- that was a real delight.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And-- and I used to look for strange birds' eggs, and I used to love to climb down into wells.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when I got found out, my grandmother got mortified and covered the well with a great big plank and a stone on top.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was an exciting, mysterious time to have been at school, and even preschool.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "A lot of time to myself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I used to climb on the roof of our house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was a chestnut tree in front of it, and one of the branches reached over.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I could then be unobserved and listen to all the people, all the grown-ups talking.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I didn't understand it, but it was a fascinating experience.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Sometimes I heard them looking for me, but I didn't say anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There was no sound out of me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I finished the four grades in Szucsi.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And then my grandparents-- there were no further school there, as I said, I was the only Jew in the school-- put me in a Jewish orphanage in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- it was-- excuse me-- very uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- part of this was my mother's overriding angst about being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was reading various reports.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Kafka was still writing in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Again, this comes to me on reflection.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At the time, I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there was a high degree of angst.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And eventually, she had to be hospitalized, where she stayed until the Germans took her out of the hospital into the ghettos in 1944.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anyhow, in 1939, I was put into the Jewish orphanage.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was a terrible shock to me at first.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "To begin with, I didn't know that I had-- I spoke Hungarian with the dialect of the village.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And kids can be very cruel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I used to say [HUNGARIAN].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And of course, they laughed at me because proper Hungarian is [HUNGARIAN].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was very miserable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- but eventually, eventually I-- I came over it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I should say that my grandparents had a Torah in our own house, and we used to have prayer services four times a year from the neighboring villages.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Jews came to form a minyan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember hiding under my grandfather's white prayer shirt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And everybody looks so fierce.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My grandfather had big red moustache, and it was twirled.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He looked fierce.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And occasionally he winked at me during the prayer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Otherwise, the whole thing was almost surreal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Then there was a wonderful cat, I remember, in the-- we had a cat, a little red cat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I used to torture him, for which now I apologize.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But-- it-- and the roosters made wonderful noises.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It was a-- it was a village life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In the orphanage, I-- I always had an ambivalent feeling about God.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I was overridden by the notion of sin and having said God's name in vain, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And in the orphanage-- it must've been the first few months, there was a synagogue in the orphanage-- I remember walking into the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was nobody there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I used to be afraid of the synagogue, and I told God that that was not a fair deal that I got.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I was not going to be afraid any longer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I can't tell you what a huge relief that was, to have done this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And eventually I made friends in the orphanage, and eventually I became myself a big boy, and other little kids looked up to me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And it was like a family, like a huge, wonderful, extended family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I still keep in touch with some of them who live in Israel and other places.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my grandparents-- I used to, in 19-- 1940, 1941 and '42, I did summer holidays I spent on the farm.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by then, they took away the farm from them, because they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they opted to-- to remain in the building, so they had one room of their house where they lived in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in 1943, I remember, I no longer went there. '43 was my bar mitzvah year.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they didn't come to my bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My grandfather must've been about 70 then, and my grandmother about 67.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I do love them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And especially my-- excuse me-- my grandmother was a very courageous lady.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There are a lot of pictures and slides that kind of envelope me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember her lighting candles Friday nights, how she was crying, and I didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She used to go and visit rabbis, and famous rabbis somewhere in eastern Hungary or Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they used to tell her what to do, and how to write things down on a paper and put it on some grave.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
